{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"373d5c0e-2c6d-468a-bd29-6890b84d11a5","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x removed VSTest support entirely.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4, `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` became the default runner, but VSTest compatibility was still available (you could set `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>`). In **MSTest.Sdk 4.x**, the VSTest integration layer was completely dropped — the test project only produces a Microsoft.Testing.Platform executable, so `vstest.console` can no longer discover or run tests.\n\n**Your options:**\n\n1. **Switch your CI to use `dotnet test`** (or run the test executable directly) — it now uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default.\n2. **If you must keep vstest.console**, pin to `MSTest.Sdk/3.8.x` until you can migrate your pipeline.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"730d1bc0-b941-486e-9852-f83d20235d8a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change between MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 and MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0 regarding test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes - I should be able to answer this from my knowledge of the MSTest ecosystem changes.\n\nIn MSTest SDK 3.x, projects could be run with both VSTest (vstest.console) and Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Starting with MSTest SDK 3.4+, the default runner switched to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, but VSTest compatibility was still available.\n\nIn MSTest SDK 4.x, VSTest support was completely removed. \n\nThe key issue is that `IsTestingPlatformApplication` is now always true in 4.x, and since VSTest integration has been stripped out entirely, vstest.console can no longer discover or run tests from these projects.","outputTokens":415,"requestId":"9825:3D4537:16A9DF9:1BA68FB:69FFF664"},"id":"b4e3e602-aa58-4d18-99f6-a78dbdbb57ad","timestamp":"2026-05-10T03:07:26.983Z","parentId":"a406a606-9903-4d2a-bfbc-63d338445e42"}
